HEADWORD: Forayer
<hw>For"ay*er</hw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ ?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who makes
or joins in a foray.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They might not choose the lowland road,⟦br⟧
For the Merse <qex>forayers</qex> were abroad.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W.
Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Forbade</ent>⟦br⟧
